An alternative result, of significant importance in the theory of stochastic calculus is the following. Given two functions and of finite variation, which are both right-continuous and have left-limits (they are càdlàg functions) then

:formula_19

where . This result can be seen as a precursor to Itô&#x27;s lemma, and is of use in the general theory of stochastic integration. The final term is which arises from the quadratic covariation of and . (The earlier result can then be seen as a result pertaining to the Stratonovich integral.)

==Related concepts==

